    <item>
      <title>Travere's Filspari (sparsentan)</title>
      <link>https://www.google.com</link>
      <description>&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Summary:&lt;/b&gt; The FDA has approved &lt;b&gt;Travere Therapeutics&lt;/b&gt;' &lt;b&gt;Filspari (sparsentan)&lt;/b&gt; as the first drug specifically for focal segmental glomerulosclerosis (FSGS), a rare kidney disease. This approval comes despite a Phase 3 trial failure, highlighting the drug's efficacy in this indication.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;MoAs:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;Sparsentan&lt;/b&gt; is a dual endothelin receptor antagonist and angiotensin II receptor blocker.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sources:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.biopharmadive.com/news/travere-fda-approve-flispari-fsgs-kidney-disease/817415/"&gt;BioPharma Dive&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.biospace.com/fda/traveres-filspari-overcomes-phase-3-fail-to-become-first-drug-for-rare-kidney-disease"&gt;BioSpace&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://endpoints.news/fda-approves-traveres-filspari-as-first-drug-for-the-kidney-disease-called-fsgs/"&gt;Endpoints News&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
